William Henry McCAUSLAND, Appellant, v. INTERNATIONAL SHOE COMPANY, Appellee. No. 7899. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit.« Oct. 17, 1935. For opinion below, see 9 F.Supp. 129. Lane & Lane, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Gold, Silk & Quittner, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, MATHEWS, and HANEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered, appeal allowed by District Court, and petition to this court, under section 24b of the Bankruptcy Act (11 U.S.C.A. § 47 (b), dismissed, thai a decree of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court issue forthwith.
